    "created_at": "2015-07-29T01:49:23Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-29T01:49:23Z",
    "body": "Electron itself uses an async handle to implement Node.js integration so that's why `process._getActiveHandles()` is ways >=1 handle.\n\nBut even if we avoid creating active handles in Node.js, the Chromium itself still maintains a quite complex message loop, which means even if there is nothing active in Node.js we might still have lots of things running in Chromium.\n"
  },
