    "updated_at": "2016-05-06T08:12:34Z",
    "body": "I'm closing this as won't fix, because even though we can check whether there is things running in Node, we can not do it for Chromium's message loops. Many tasks of Chromium are designed to run forever, so the state of message loop can only be always running.\n"
